1
00:00:45,713 --> 00:00:47,590
CHAPTER 32:
A VARIABLE CALLED NA DEUL-I

2
00:00:47,673 --> 00:00:49,842
-How have you been?
-Good.

3
00:00:51,510 --> 00:00:53,387
You seem to be doing well too.
I'm happy for you.

4
00:00:57,475 --> 00:01:00,352
To tell the truth,
I was surprised to hear from you.

5
00:01:00,436 --> 00:01:01,437
Pleased too.

6
00:01:02,855 --> 00:01:05,149
You could have gotten in touch yourself.

7
00:01:10,613 --> 00:01:11,697
Are you doing better now?

8
00:01:12,281 --> 00:01:13,449
Yeah.

9
00:01:13,532 --> 00:01:16,368
When I heard you had a surgery,
I was really worried.

10
00:01:16,452 --> 00:01:17,745
And I couldn't get hold of you.

11
00:01:20,289 --> 00:01:21,791
I'm sorry I didn't say anything.

12
00:01:22,458 --> 00:01:24,210
I was in shock.

13
00:01:25,169 --> 00:01:26,378
And I was really upset too.

14
00:01:28,088 --> 00:01:29,882
I can't believe you majored in Education
and became a teacher.

15
00:01:30,341 --> 00:01:31,342
It was so unexpected.

16
00:01:31,425 --> 00:01:33,844
I was sure you'd stick with research.

17
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:57,952
Eui-ju?

18
00:01:58,619 --> 00:01:59,453
What are you doing here?

19
00:01:59,537 --> 00:02:00,871
EPISODE 10

20
00:02:01,872 --> 00:02:02,748
Sir.

21
00:02:02,832 --> 00:02:05,417
Oh, I was just doing some studying,

22
00:02:05,501 --> 00:02:06,919
but it's time to go home.

23
00:02:07,002 --> 00:02:08,294
Eui-ju.

24
00:02:08,378 --> 00:02:10,840
Have you finally decided
to put some effort into your studies?

25
00:02:11,549 --> 00:02:12,383
Yes.

26
00:02:15,886 --> 00:02:17,638
What brought you here, Mr. Ha?

27
00:02:18,264 --> 00:02:19,348
Is that Mr. Ga?

28
00:02:20,683 --> 00:02:22,184
What do we have here?

29
00:02:22,268 --> 00:02:25,103
My dear Mr. Ga, the standoffish robot,
is enjoying coffee with someone.

30
00:02:25,187 --> 00:02:26,313
With a lady friend, no less.

31
00:02:27,648 --> 00:02:28,774
Hang on a second.

32
00:02:29,483 --> 00:02:30,484
By any chance…

33
00:02:32,528 --> 00:02:34,405
You're Professor Na Deul-i, right?

34
00:02:36,699 --> 00:02:37,741
Yes, that's me.

35
00:02:39,285 --> 00:02:40,953
I knew it. I saw you on the news.

36
00:02:41,036 --> 00:02:44,665
I was touched by the interview you gave
after winning the Fields Medal.

37
00:02:44,748 --> 00:02:46,333
Oh, thank you.

38
00:02:47,459 --> 00:02:48,586
Where are my manners?

39
00:02:48,668 --> 00:02:51,297
It's nice to meet you.
I'm a colleague of Mr. Ga's.

40
00:02:51,380 --> 00:02:53,591
My name is Ha E-den. It's such a pleasure.

41
00:02:59,513 --> 00:03:03,976
Anyhow, how do you know Mr. Ga?

42
00:03:05,477 --> 00:03:06,312
We're friends.

43
00:03:06,395 --> 00:03:09,857
Friends. I see.

44
00:03:09,940 --> 00:03:11,942
When a man and woman
meet in a cafe on the weekend,

45
00:03:12,026 --> 00:03:13,944
it's a date 99% of the time, no?

46
00:03:15,988 --> 00:03:16,822
Shall we get going?

47
00:03:17,364 --> 00:03:18,198
-Yes.
-Okay.

48
00:03:18,282 --> 00:03:21,952
You two look great together.

49
00:03:22,036 --> 00:03:23,996
You make a great couple.

50
00:03:24,079 --> 00:03:25,122
See you again soon.

51
00:03:25,204 --> 00:03:26,457
-Oh, sure.
-Take care.

52
00:03:27,416 --> 00:03:28,834
As for you, study hard!

53
00:03:28,918 --> 00:03:31,003
If you want to become
as great as Professor Na.

54
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:33,005
Get home safely.

55
00:03:36,759 --> 00:03:37,676
Hop on.

56
00:03:38,469 --> 00:03:39,428
Thank you.

57
00:03:40,137 --> 00:03:41,180
Hello.

58
00:03:42,430 --> 00:03:44,350
My name is Yeo Eui-ju.

59
00:03:44,433 --> 00:03:47,144
Mr. Ga is my homeroom teacher.

60
00:03:47,978 --> 00:03:50,356
I see. Hello.

61
00:03:51,065 --> 00:03:52,775
Wow, that's amazing.

62
00:03:52,858 --> 00:03:54,692
I can't believe
you have a student of your own.

63
00:03:56,028 --> 00:03:58,822
Were you at college with Mr. Ga?

64
00:03:58,906 --> 00:04:01,450
No, we've been friends
since middle school.

65
00:04:02,242 --> 00:04:04,078
I see. Middle school?

66
00:04:05,162 --> 00:04:06,163
That's a long time.

67
00:04:06,246 --> 00:04:07,414
You'd best get going.

68
00:04:08,290 --> 00:04:09,667
About that thing I suggested.

69
00:04:10,334 --> 00:04:11,543
You'll give it some thought?

70
00:04:12,962 --> 00:04:14,254
I'm not sure.

71
00:04:14,922 --> 00:04:16,757
Are you playing hard to get or what?

72
00:04:17,716 --> 00:04:18,676
Get going already.

73
00:04:18,759 --> 00:04:20,427
All right.

74
00:04:20,511 --> 00:04:22,638
Until next time, Eui-ju.

75
00:04:23,389 --> 00:04:25,224
Okay, goodbye.

76
00:04:25,307 --> 00:04:26,433
Drive safe.

77
00:04:39,279 --> 00:04:41,573
Mr. Ga, your friend

78
00:04:41,657 --> 00:04:43,200
seems really nice.

79
00:04:43,283 --> 00:04:46,537
She's pretty, and she seems really kind.

80
00:04:47,204 --> 00:04:49,665
And she even won the Fields Medal.

81
00:04:49,748 --> 00:04:51,250
That's so cool.

82
00:04:51,332 --> 00:04:52,876
I wish I had a friend like that.

83
00:04:54,253 --> 00:04:56,588
I bet she's super popular.

84
00:04:56,672 --> 00:04:58,257
She must have a boyfriend, right?

85
00:04:59,133 --> 00:05:02,803
Would it be difficult to find someone
when you're as perfect as her?

86
00:05:02,886 --> 00:05:04,888
When you're good at everything,

87
00:05:04,972 --> 00:05:07,933
people would always compare
your partner to you,

88
00:05:08,017 --> 00:05:10,394
making them feel insecure.

89
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:14,023
What are you trying to say?

90
00:05:15,399 --> 00:05:16,859
It's just

91
00:05:16,942 --> 00:05:20,863
I was wondering what kind of guy
someone so amazing would date.

92
00:05:21,905 --> 00:05:22,740
Why?

93
00:05:25,325 --> 00:05:28,245
If you don't get more than 50 points
in the upcoming math exam,

94
00:05:29,079 --> 00:05:31,540
I'm telling your parents about your novel
at our parent-teacher meeting.

95
00:05:33,917 --> 00:05:34,752
Sorry?

96
00:05:35,544 --> 00:05:37,212
Come on, that's not fair.

97
00:05:37,296 --> 00:05:39,548
Sir, you won't really, will you?

98
00:05:39,631 --> 00:05:41,175
Please tell me you won't. Come on.

99
00:05:43,093 --> 00:05:44,636
Sir!

100
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:48,515
I'll try my best,
but 50 points in math is a tall order.

101
00:05:50,225 --> 00:05:54,146
Sir, that thing your friend
was talking about just now.

102
00:05:54,897 --> 00:05:56,732
What did she want you to think over?

103
00:05:57,524 --> 00:05:59,026
It's not really any of your business.

104
00:05:59,818 --> 00:06:01,904
Would it kill you to be nicer?

105
00:06:03,739 --> 00:06:04,740
Don't forget my coke.

106
00:06:05,616 --> 00:06:06,825
Just a moment, sir.

107
00:06:07,451 --> 00:06:09,036
I'll be right back.

108
00:06:09,912 --> 00:06:11,455
Hold up.

109
00:06:11,538 --> 00:06:13,123
Don't go.

110
00:06:13,207 --> 00:06:14,291
Wait for me, okay?

111
00:06:23,425 --> 00:06:24,426
Got it.

112
00:06:27,304 --> 00:06:29,515
Don't forget the factors
associated with constipation.

113
00:06:30,432 --> 00:06:32,851
I hope you won't end up back in the ER.

114
00:06:32,935 --> 00:06:34,394
It's not for me.

115
00:06:34,478 --> 00:06:35,854
It's for my little brother.

116
00:06:36,605 --> 00:06:37,564
You're a great sister.

117
00:06:39,108 --> 00:06:41,068
What, getting blackmailed
into doing his bidding?

118
00:06:41,735 --> 00:06:43,153
What does he have on you?

119
00:06:44,279 --> 00:06:48,033
Only two people found out about my secret.

120
00:06:50,077 --> 00:06:53,831
As usual, I was engrossed
in writing my novel…

121
00:06:55,874 --> 00:06:57,292
and talking to others online.

122
00:07:01,630 --> 00:07:05,175
Hey, I've got a random question.
What do you have our group chat saved as?

123
00:07:05,259 --> 00:07:07,094
Beautiful Life. BL.

124
00:07:07,177 --> 00:07:08,470
Real Estate Chat for me.

125
00:07:08,554 --> 00:07:10,764
Because sometimes,
my hubby looks at my phone.

126
00:07:12,266 --> 00:07:15,060
This is a rough draft
of something I'm working on.

127
00:07:15,144 --> 00:07:17,396
The characters
are a young master and his servant.

128
00:07:17,479 --> 00:07:18,730
Let me know what you think.

129
00:07:21,108 --> 00:07:22,609
That's such a great character dynamic.

130
00:07:23,610 --> 00:07:25,946
I don't get why your stuff
isn't more popular, Imuk.

131
00:07:26,029 --> 00:07:27,531
It's such a shame.

132
00:07:28,866 --> 00:07:32,161
Just imagine the beautiful young master
being heartbroken over the aloof servant.

133
00:07:33,120 --> 00:07:34,746
That just shot chills down my spine.

134
00:07:44,047 --> 00:07:44,965
I think

135
00:07:45,924 --> 00:07:49,720
there's someone behind me.

136
00:07:50,596 --> 00:07:51,722
Can it be a ghost?

137
00:07:52,431 --> 00:07:54,224
It'd be better if it were.

138
00:07:54,308 --> 00:07:56,018
If it's your parents, I'll pray for you.

139
00:08:23,045 --> 00:08:24,087
Did you see anything?

140
00:08:27,341 --> 00:08:30,761
Still, at least it wasn't my parents.

141
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:33,722
But I do have to keep buying him coke
whenever he wants it.

142
00:08:35,057 --> 00:08:36,265
Why do you like it so much?

143
00:08:37,517 --> 00:08:39,019
I'm not sure.

144
00:08:39,102 --> 00:08:40,770
People like what they like.

145
00:08:42,688 --> 00:08:44,900
I guess that's why you kept writing
despite bombing every time.

146
00:08:45,943 --> 00:08:48,654
I always thought I'd hit it big
if I just kept on writing.

147
00:08:51,949 --> 00:08:53,492
That's unfounded confidence.

148
00:08:53,575 --> 00:08:56,870
If there were a basis for it,
that'd be a prophecy, not confidence.

149
00:08:57,913 --> 00:09:00,457
I'll keep at it,

150
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:01,875
and I will get better.

151
00:09:05,754 --> 00:09:06,964
Sir.

152
00:09:07,047 --> 00:09:08,423
You know,

153
00:09:09,216 --> 00:09:11,301
back when EBC's crew came by to shoot,

154
00:09:11,927 --> 00:09:14,304
you didn't finish your answer
to my questions.

155
00:09:16,265 --> 00:09:19,351
I'm curious why you decided
to become a teacher.

156
00:09:37,035 --> 00:09:38,370
How was hanging out with your friend?

157
00:09:39,162 --> 00:09:40,038
Good.

158
00:09:44,251 --> 00:09:45,877
She's back for the first time in years

159
00:09:45,961 --> 00:09:47,754
and being feted
for winning the Fields Medal.

160
00:09:47,838 --> 00:09:50,757
And yet, she took the time
to come to Jeonju to see you.

161
00:09:50,841 --> 00:09:52,134
Why would she do that?

162
00:09:52,217 --> 00:09:54,469
This wasn't exactly a reunion
with your old Olympiad team.

163
00:09:54,553 --> 00:09:55,595
She came to see just you.

164
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:56,888
No one else but you.

165
00:09:56,972 --> 00:09:58,265
Why is that?

166
00:09:59,099 --> 00:10:02,728
Did you share a warm and precious memory
from when you were both young?

167
00:10:02,811 --> 00:10:04,062
Did they use to date?

168
00:10:05,022 --> 00:10:07,190
That's the only explanation.

169
00:10:07,274 --> 00:10:10,402
When it comes to men and women,
it's all about the chemistry.

170
00:10:10,485 --> 00:10:13,071
There needs to be that spark

171
00:10:13,155 --> 00:10:16,616
for you to want to see that person again
after years have passed.

172
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:18,201
-You know what I'm saying?
-True that.

173
00:10:18,285 --> 00:10:19,119
Mind your own business.

174
00:10:21,621 --> 00:10:22,706
Looks like you're right.

175
00:10:23,665 --> 00:10:24,499
Dude!

176
00:10:24,583 --> 00:10:26,043
I thought all you ever did was study.

177
00:10:27,627 --> 00:10:28,712
My guess is that

178
00:10:28,795 --> 00:10:32,049
Woo-su and this girl Deul-i

179
00:10:32,132 --> 00:10:34,801
hit it off at the Olympiad,
started dating, and then broke up.

180
00:10:34,885 --> 00:10:36,678
-No way.
-Hear me out.

181
00:10:36,762 --> 00:10:39,097
That must be why he dropped out.

182
00:10:39,181 --> 00:10:43,143
The thought of seeing his ex-girlfriend
pained his heart too much.

183
00:10:43,226 --> 00:10:44,936
-Been there.
-Just the thought

184
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:46,438
upset him so much

185
00:10:46,521 --> 00:10:48,315
that he couldn't face it.

186
00:10:49,066 --> 00:10:53,236
Even our cold-hearted Woo-su
once felt the flicker of true love.

187
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,196
Or something like that.

188
00:10:55,447 --> 00:10:56,573
I'm so proud of him.

189
00:10:56,656 --> 00:10:57,866
Still, he wouldn't just quit.

190
00:10:58,575 --> 00:10:59,618
Of course, he would.

191
00:11:00,494 --> 00:11:02,329
Why? Because they were rivals.

192
00:11:03,038 --> 00:11:04,122
Woo-su would have said,

193
00:11:07,042 --> 00:11:08,251
"I'll pull out

194
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:10,754
so you can reach for the stars."
Or some such.

195
00:11:11,380 --> 00:11:12,506
Only one of them could win.

196
00:11:12,589 --> 00:11:16,551
You're saying Woo-su
gave up on math for a girl?

197
00:11:18,178 --> 00:11:20,931
Well, there was another reason as well.

198
00:11:22,140 --> 00:11:23,225
What?

199
00:11:25,811 --> 00:11:26,728
That thing.

200
00:11:27,562 --> 00:11:28,563
His phobia of being filmed.

201
00:11:29,981 --> 00:11:31,066
He feared finishing first.

202
00:11:37,406 --> 00:11:39,408
"Wow, that's amazing."

203
00:11:39,491 --> 00:11:41,159
"I can't believe
you have a student of your own."

204
00:11:42,953 --> 00:11:45,288
What's so amazing about that?

205
00:11:45,372 --> 00:11:47,415
Is it really so amazing
for a teacher to have students?

206
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,460
Until next time, Eui-ju.

207
00:11:51,962 --> 00:11:52,879
"Next time"?

208
00:11:55,298 --> 00:11:56,133
Sure.

209
00:11:57,592 --> 00:11:59,302
Maybe we will meet again.

210
00:12:14,025 --> 00:12:17,362
WE WERE FRIENDS, EPISODE 7

211
00:12:32,377 --> 00:12:33,253
Who are you?

212
00:12:38,550 --> 00:12:39,551
Me?

213
00:12:40,218 --> 00:12:41,761
I'm the Chairwoman's secretary, Na Ran-i.

214
00:12:42,762 --> 00:12:46,433
As long as she pays me,
I take care of all her dirty work.

215
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:49,811
She wants me to get you away from Si-on.

216
00:12:51,021 --> 00:12:52,898
As much as I appreciate your pretty face…

217
00:12:54,274 --> 00:12:55,567
This is it for you.

218
00:12:56,151 --> 00:12:57,277
No. Don't do it!

219
00:13:05,911 --> 00:13:07,746
Yoon!

220
00:13:08,747 --> 00:13:09,831
How did you find me?

221
00:13:41,696 --> 00:13:42,531
Yoon!

222
00:13:50,121 --> 00:13:50,997
Are you okay?

223
00:13:54,584 --> 00:13:55,835
I'm fine.

224
00:13:58,964 --> 00:14:01,174
SI-ON LOWERED HIMSELF TO MEET YOON'S EYES

225
00:14:01,758 --> 00:14:02,842
Let's get out of here.

226
00:14:05,554 --> 00:14:09,015
SO CLOSE AND SO INTENSE,
HIS GAZE MADE YOON'S HEART RACE

227
00:14:14,479 --> 00:14:16,231
JUST THEN, RAN-I CALLED OUT

228
00:14:16,314 --> 00:14:17,399
How amusing.

229
00:14:18,900 --> 00:14:21,111
Let's see how long you can keep this up.

230
00:14:21,736 --> 00:14:23,905
RAN-I'S COMMENT
PROVOKED YOON'S WILDER NATURE

231
00:14:23,989 --> 00:14:24,990
Just a moment.

232
00:14:26,074 --> 00:14:27,742
I refuse to be in anyone's debt.

233
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:30,161
No!

234
00:14:30,245 --> 00:14:32,163
-Don't!
-Let it…

235
00:14:33,832 --> 00:14:35,458
YOON BID HER FAREWELL

236
00:14:35,542 --> 00:14:39,838
IT WAS FOR SI-ON, OF ALL PEOPLE

237
00:14:47,053 --> 00:14:50,223
CHAPTER 33:
SOMETHING UTTERLY USELESS

238
00:14:51,057 --> 00:14:52,767
-Eun Ha-su.
-Here.

239
00:14:53,435 --> 00:14:54,769
-Oh A-rin.
-Here.

240
00:14:55,395 --> 00:14:56,771
-Choi Yu-mi.
-Here.

241
00:14:57,689 --> 00:14:59,441
-Yeo Eui-ju.
-Here.

242
00:15:00,025 --> 00:15:01,818
-Choi Go-ya.
-Here.

243
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:02,736
Choi Ji-a.

244
00:15:07,449 --> 00:15:08,617
-Hong Su-min.
-Here.

245
00:15:08,700 --> 00:15:10,660
-Jeon Chae-won.
-Here.

246
00:15:10,744 --> 00:15:12,537
-Im Su-yeon.
-Here.

247
00:15:22,005 --> 00:15:23,423
-Im Su-yeon.
-Here.

248
00:15:23,506 --> 00:15:25,175
-Lee Eun-ji.
-Here.

249
00:15:25,258 --> 00:15:26,509
-Choi Hye-jeong.
-Here.

250
00:15:28,345 --> 00:15:29,596
I hope you're all ready for class.

251
00:15:31,723 --> 00:15:33,350
-I smell alcohol.
-What on earth?

252
00:15:33,433 --> 00:15:34,768
-It's definitely alcohol.
-What's this?

253
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:44,944
Quiet.

254
00:15:48,365 --> 00:15:49,407
Who's on cleaning duty today?

255
00:15:50,283 --> 00:15:51,451
Me, sir.

256
00:15:52,827 --> 00:15:54,120
-Eui-ju.
-Yes, sir?

257
00:15:54,746 --> 00:15:56,748
-Clean up again.
-Yes, sir.

258
00:15:56,831 --> 00:15:58,958
-Let's air out the room. Open the windows.
-But it's cold.

259
00:16:03,213 --> 00:16:04,381
Ji-a, go to the nurse's office.

260
00:16:24,025 --> 00:16:25,193
Morning to you too.

261
00:16:31,574 --> 00:16:32,450
Hey!

262
00:16:43,628 --> 00:16:44,963
Mr. Ga.

263
00:16:45,046 --> 00:16:47,006
She's in your class, right?

264
00:16:47,090 --> 00:16:49,634
Are you aware she's come to school drunk?

265
00:16:50,218 --> 00:16:52,679
Goodness me.

266
00:16:52,762 --> 00:16:56,433
How can a student come to school
reeking of alcohol?

267
00:17:01,604 --> 00:17:05,358
You're the one who wasn't in her uniform
when the EBC crew was here filming.

268
00:17:05,442 --> 00:17:08,569
Are you taking school seriously?

269
00:17:08,653 --> 00:17:13,031
Ms. Kim, let me get back to you
after hearing Ji-a's side of the story.

270
00:17:14,492 --> 00:17:15,910
Mr. Ga.

271
00:17:15,993 --> 00:17:18,496
This student is drunk.

272
00:17:18,579 --> 00:17:20,749
What is there to understand?

273
00:17:23,960 --> 00:17:25,127
Step out for a moment.

274
00:17:33,094 --> 00:17:35,388
I don't want to butt heads
with you over nothing.

275
00:17:36,848 --> 00:17:39,851
I finally got rid of that knot yesterday,
and I'm starting to tense up again.

276
00:17:41,603 --> 00:17:45,356
Ji-a's background differs somewhat
from that of other students.

277
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:46,900
She has no parental support.

278
00:17:46,983 --> 00:17:49,569
She's staying at a youth shelter
and must earn a living herself.

279
00:17:49,652 --> 00:17:53,281
Despite that,
she still has a strong desire to learn.

280
00:17:53,364 --> 00:17:55,241
Really?

281
00:17:55,325 --> 00:17:56,659
That's great.

282
00:17:56,743 --> 00:17:59,078
Then, she'll surely do well
at another school.

283
00:17:59,662 --> 00:18:01,498
She might seem tough,
but she's still just a child.

284
00:18:04,250 --> 00:18:06,920
As her homeroom teacher,
I'd like to personally make sure

285
00:18:07,504 --> 00:18:09,589
she turns her life around.

286
00:18:10,673 --> 00:18:12,091
Please allow me that opportunity.

287
00:18:12,175 --> 00:18:13,468
Mr. Ga.

288
00:18:13,551 --> 00:18:15,470
Do you recall our school motto?

289
00:18:16,221 --> 00:18:19,140
It's "Aim for the Elite."

290
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:22,101
I can't seem to imagine her career choices

291
00:18:22,185 --> 00:18:25,313
or her life goals of any kind

292
00:18:26,022 --> 00:18:27,857
being anywhere near that ideal.

293
00:18:28,358 --> 00:18:31,110
In other words,
she's not a good fit for this school.

294
00:18:32,612 --> 00:18:34,155
You may leave.

295
00:18:44,249 --> 00:18:47,001
Does he think he's a crusader for justice?

296
00:18:47,085 --> 00:18:50,421
Of all the students to stick up for,
he chose the one who showed up drunk.

297
00:18:51,047 --> 00:18:52,257
How obnoxious.

298
00:18:53,424 --> 00:18:56,135
Would you believe
he's friends with Na Deul-i?

299
00:18:56,219 --> 00:18:57,720
Who is Na Deul-i?

300
00:18:57,804 --> 00:18:59,889
Don't you know, Aunt Young-hee?

301
00:18:59,973 --> 00:19:02,642
She's the Fields Medal winner.
Apparently, they're friends.

302
00:19:03,810 --> 00:19:04,978
What?

303
00:19:05,520 --> 00:19:07,981
You're unbelievable.

304
00:19:08,064 --> 00:19:10,066
Why are you only mentioning this now?

305
00:19:10,149 --> 00:19:11,776
When else did I have the chance?

306
00:19:17,907 --> 00:19:18,783
Ji-a.

307
00:19:22,829 --> 00:19:23,663
Why did you do it?

308
00:19:26,082 --> 00:19:28,334
It's wrong for a student
to come to school drunk.

309
00:19:31,337 --> 00:19:33,840
Anyone can make a mistake.
It's what's next that's important.

310
00:19:33,923 --> 00:19:38,177
Write an essay stating what you did wrong
and what you're going to do about it.

311
00:19:38,803 --> 00:19:40,680
I will show it to the principal.

312
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:43,057
Yes, sir.

313
00:19:44,017 --> 00:19:46,352
I'll get you a lighter punishment,
so be sure to wear your uniform

314
00:19:46,436 --> 00:19:47,478
and don't skip class

315
00:19:48,313 --> 00:19:49,272
or get into any trouble.

316
00:19:50,315 --> 00:19:51,232
Yes, sir.

317
00:19:57,322 --> 00:19:58,990
-That's for sure.
-I can't take it.

318
00:19:59,073 --> 00:19:59,908
Eui-ju, over here!

319
00:19:59,991 --> 00:20:01,743
Eui-ju, quickly!

320
00:20:02,785 --> 00:20:05,079
-I don't know.
-This is so good.

321
00:20:05,163 --> 00:20:06,497
-Try it. It's incredible.
-Let's see.

322
00:20:06,581 --> 00:20:07,790
Where are you off to, Go-ya?

323
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:10,710
Can I sit here?

324
00:20:12,295 --> 00:20:13,630
Sit down, Eui-ju.

325
00:20:13,713 --> 00:20:14,714
Okay.

326
00:20:17,425 --> 00:20:19,636
The food is so good today!

327
00:20:20,637 --> 00:20:22,263
Eat up. It's delish.

328
00:20:26,184 --> 00:20:27,560
Can I have a minute, Go-ya?

329
00:20:31,773 --> 00:20:33,399
Go-ya, where are you going?

330
00:20:34,776 --> 00:20:36,819
-I have huge news.
-What is it?

331
00:20:36,903 --> 00:20:39,072
Young-hee wanted to expel Ji-a,

332
00:20:39,155 --> 00:20:41,074
but Mr. Ga stopped her.

333
00:20:41,157 --> 00:20:42,659
-Really?
-That's amazing.

334
00:20:42,742 --> 00:20:43,910
Seems like it's on hold.

335
00:20:44,786 --> 00:20:48,164
Gosh. How did he manage that?

336
00:20:48,247 --> 00:20:49,832
He must have some kind of leverage.

337
00:20:51,834 --> 00:20:54,337
When are you going to make up with Go-ya?

338
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:57,131
I have to say everything twice.

339
00:20:57,215 --> 00:20:58,383
It sucks.

340
00:20:58,466 --> 00:21:02,762
Is Go-ya still refusing to talk to you?

341
00:21:03,721 --> 00:21:04,555
Yeah.

342
00:21:05,348 --> 00:21:08,810
What did you guys argue about, anyway?

343
00:21:11,604 --> 00:21:12,855
Argue?

344
00:21:13,481 --> 00:21:14,649
We didn't argue.

345
00:21:14,732 --> 00:21:17,193
-What is it?
-Oh, please.

346
00:21:17,276 --> 00:21:18,653
Just tell us.

347
00:21:27,787 --> 00:21:29,747
I have a research idea
I'd like to work on with you.

348
00:21:33,001 --> 00:21:35,628
You were always
the most interesting person to talk to.

349
00:21:37,964 --> 00:21:39,757
I don't know how long it will take,

350
00:21:39,841 --> 00:21:41,801
but I really want to work with you

351
00:21:42,385 --> 00:21:44,303
on the topology
of algebraic curves and surfaces.

352
00:21:48,683 --> 00:21:49,851
Why that topic?

353
00:21:51,310 --> 00:21:53,604
I'm not sure. It just drew me in.

354
00:21:54,313 --> 00:21:55,898
I was looking
for something utterly useless.

355
00:21:59,819 --> 00:22:01,070
Remember that Hardy quote?

356
00:22:01,154 --> 00:22:04,157
"No discovery of mine has made,
or is likely to make,

357
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:06,451
directly or indirectly,

358
00:22:06,534 --> 00:22:08,202
for good or ill,

359
00:22:08,286 --> 00:22:10,413
the least difference

360
00:22:10,496 --> 00:22:12,165
to the amenity of the world."

361
00:22:12,665 --> 00:22:13,499
"I have

362
00:22:13,583 --> 00:22:17,086
-never done anything useful."
-"…never done anything useful."

363
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:23,843
That's my next goal.

364
00:22:24,510 --> 00:22:26,387
Accomplishing something utterly useless.

365
00:22:43,696 --> 00:22:44,822
Where are you going?

366
00:22:44,906 --> 00:22:45,740
For a walk.

367
00:22:46,365 --> 00:22:48,785
I'll go with you.
I need to walk off my dinner.

368
00:22:51,287 --> 00:22:52,830
Are you still getting bad headaches?

369
00:22:52,914 --> 00:22:53,748
Sometimes.

370
00:22:54,499 --> 00:22:55,958
Shouldn't you see a doctor?

371
00:22:56,042 --> 00:22:57,210
It's not that bad.

372
00:22:57,835 --> 00:22:59,462
Just go anyway.

373
00:22:59,545 --> 00:23:01,297
There's no harm in getting checked out.

374
00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:02,548
Fine. I'll go.

375
00:23:03,341 --> 00:23:05,009
No empty promises, all right?

376
00:23:05,093 --> 00:23:06,135
Make sure you go.

377
00:23:07,178 --> 00:23:08,054
Okay.

378
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:21,275
Get me a coke on your way home.

379
00:23:23,694 --> 00:23:26,864
I'm already home.

380
00:23:30,034 --> 00:23:31,494
I'm in my room.

381
00:23:31,577 --> 00:23:33,162
Can I get it tomorrow instead?

382
00:23:35,039 --> 00:23:36,040
Mom!

383
00:23:36,124 --> 00:23:37,708
I have something to tell you.

384
00:23:37,792 --> 00:23:39,210
Hey, Eui-do!

385
00:23:39,293 --> 00:23:41,170
Okay, Eui-do. I get it, all right?

386
00:23:41,254 --> 00:23:42,171
I'll go now.

387
00:24:02,775 --> 00:24:04,735
About that proposal
from your friend Deul-i.

388
00:24:05,403 --> 00:24:06,404
What do you think?

389
00:24:07,029 --> 00:24:07,905
Be honest.

390
00:24:08,698 --> 00:24:10,449
I don't know. I'm not interested.

391
00:24:11,284 --> 00:24:12,160
Liar.

392
00:24:13,161 --> 00:24:14,871
You answered too quickly

393
00:24:14,954 --> 00:24:16,038
like you'd rehearsed it.

394
00:24:17,707 --> 00:24:21,544
I wish you'd do what you really want to.

395
00:24:22,712 --> 00:24:25,006
So seize this opportunity
and go to the US.

396
00:24:25,089 --> 00:24:26,382
Go do the research you want to do

397
00:24:27,258 --> 00:24:28,176
before it's too late.

398
00:24:29,719 --> 00:24:31,137
Are you going to the US?

399
00:25:08,758 --> 00:25:10,301
It's late. Go home.

400
00:25:10,384 --> 00:25:11,219
I don't want to.

401
00:25:11,302 --> 00:25:13,179
To tell the truth, I…

402
00:25:13,262 --> 00:25:14,931
I told you
I never wanted to see you again.

403
00:25:15,014 --> 00:25:16,265
What am I going to do now?

404
00:25:16,974 --> 00:25:18,059
How come you're here?

405
00:25:18,142 --> 00:25:19,310
Sir! What do we do?

406
00:25:19,393 --> 00:25:21,229
Why isn't she answering?

407
00:25:21,312 --> 00:25:22,438
Why isn't she even checking?

408
00:25:22,521 --> 00:25:24,732
-Hurry up and leave.
-Sir!

409
00:25:24,815 --> 00:25:26,609
I see you still haven't figured me out.

410
00:25:26,692 --> 00:25:28,903
"You're going down for real then."

411
00:25:28,986 --> 00:25:30,154
So cool.

412
00:25:30,238 --> 00:25:32,907
He's so cool.

413
00:25:32,990 --> 00:25:33,950
Tell him how you feel.

414
00:25:34,033 --> 00:25:36,327
To show him how serious you are,
look him in the eye.

415
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:37,787
-I…
-For at least three seconds.

416
00:25:38,621 --> 00:25:40,164
Look him in the eye for three seconds.

417
00:26:36,595 --> 00:26:38,597
Subtitle: Paul Carver
